//    A little experiment with Concave polyhedron  SDFs.

//    The motivation was to be able to use triangle meshes in CSG ops with other SDFs.

//    Polyhedron  must be a closed non intersecting mesh. 

//    Some artifacs appear at narrow or coplanar faces (fixed) 

//    Defined as a collection of triangles, yeah like a stl donit.

//    For each calculationg a pair of unsigned distance and one inside/outside number. 

//    Basically the closest triangle get first shot to call inside/outside.

//        but there are some edgecases that requires extra bits

//        some logic v=  abs(v1.x-v.x)<0.001? (v1.y>v.y?v1:v):     v1.x<=v.x?v1:v; 

//    Generally sound sdf, some edge leakage and some GLSL issues.  

//    In demo Polyhedra is differenced by sphere and smooth unioned with 
//    ground plane to showcase full sdf capabilites

